Cottonwood Creek Flow to Floodplain Habitat Area Relationship

A dataset containing the floodplain habitat area in acres as a function of flow in cubic feet per second

cottonwood_creek_floodplain

Format

dataframe with 10 rows and 3 variables:

flow_cfs

integer flow value in cubic feet per second

floodplain_acres

fall run floodplain acreage (use for Steelhead when needed)

watershed

name of watershed

Source

FWS

Details

The habitat area was derived from the FWS 2017 HEC-RAS 1D model.
